Project 0
Files included:
1. lab0.c: the source file
2. Makefile: used to build program, check, and generate tarball
3. backtrace.png/breakpoint.png: screen snapshots of gdb
4. README: brief introduction of the files and functions

The function can be run in the shell by:
$ gcc -g -o lab0 lab0.c
$ ./lab0 [--input=input_file] [--output=output_file] [--segfault] [--catch]

Also, you can use Makefile to compile, check and generate tarball. The corresponding codes are:
 
>> make default : compile the resource file

>> make check : automatically check the functions including:
		1. Input Option ; Check Result: The input redirection is successful.
		2. Output Option ; Check Result: The output redirection is successful.
		3. Unrecognized Option ; Check Result: When an unknown option is passed to the function, it will show that "Find the unrecognized argument."
		4. Open File ; Check Result: When an inexistent file is passed to the input option, it will show that "Find the problem in file open."
		5. Create File ; Check Result: When system cannot create the output file, it will show that "Find the problem in file create."
		6. SIGSEGV Catch ; Check Result: When --segfault and --catch options are set, the result will show that "Successfully Receive SIGSEGV".

>> make clean : remove all the files generated by check

>> make dist : build the distribution tarball		 